latestPosts.caption:
It’s Papa’s birthday today.

Two of my favourite memories with him are the simplest ones — wrapping myself around his leg like a koala every time he had to leave the house, hoping to make him stay a little longer. And the bedtime stories he told us every night — especially the ones about a tiger.

I’ve never seen my father struggle. By the time I was born, the hardest parts were behind him. But I’ve heard enough to know how much he’s been through. The kind of struggle where you don’t know where to start, where you feel lost but keep moving forward because there’s no other option. He did it with nothing. And somehow, he did it all with love and courage.

He teaches me every day, not through instructions, but by example. To work hard, to make time for the things I love, to create with my hands, to stay kind, to stay open, to unlearn and relearn.

He’s my partner in crime. My fellow dad-joke enthusiast. The one who gets me like no one else.

I hope to grow into someone even a fraction as passionate as him, someone who believes so fiercely in what they love that they’re willing to fight for it, build it from nothing, and give their whole soul to it. Someone who never lets the world harden them, who stays soft, open, generous — even when it’s hard. Someone who keeps showing up, again and again, with courage. Because that’s who he is. And that’s who I hope to become.

Papa, one day, I will make you proud, happy birthday ♥️
